main event: Two objects with wings shaped like 'boomerangs' were observed flying in a straight line from East to West, then hovered at an altitude of 100ft for about 2-3 seconds before disappearing.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on a dark night with a clear sky and visible stars., The objects were grey in color and smaller than a small plane., The sighting lasted approximately 2-3 seconds., There was no noise associated with the objects., The objects did not leave a trail.
witness description: A maintenance mechanic, aged 23, stationed at Eglin AFB.
